Steps to implement the project is :

The required packages for the above AI Resume Screening & Candidate Ranking System are:

Required Python Packages:
Streamlit – For building the web application
Pandas – For handling and displaying data
PyPDF2 – For extracting text from PDF resumes
Scikit-learn – For vectorization (TF-IDF) and similarity calculation
Install the Required Packages:
Run the following command in your terminal or command prompt to install all dependencies:
pip install streamlit pandas PyPDF2 scikit-learn
Once installed, you can run the Streamlit app using:
streamlit run your_script.py
Steps to Implement the AI Resume Screening & Candidate Ranking System
Follow these steps to set up and run the resume screening system on your local machine:
Step 1: Install Required Packages
Open your terminal or command prompt and run the following command to install all required Python packages:
pip install streamlit pandas PyPDF2 scikit-learn
Step 2: Create a Python Script
Open a code editor (e.g., VS Code, PyCharm, or Notepad++).
Create a new Python file, e.g., resume_ranker.py.
Copy and paste the full code provided in the previous response into this file.
Step 3: Run the Streamlit Application
After saving the file, navigate to the directory where your resume_ranker.py script is located using the terminal or command prompt.
Run the following command:
streamlit run resume_ranker.py
Step 4: Use the Web Application
A browser window will open automatically with the Streamlit interface.
Enter the job description in the text box.
Upload PDF resumes by clicking the "Upload PDF files" button.
View the ranked results – The system will rank the resumes based on how well they match the job description.
Check "Best Matches" – If a resume scores above the threshold (default: 0.5), it will be highlighted as a "✅ Good Match".
